edu.umw.cpsc.collegediversity
Class Student

java.lang.Object
  edu.umw.cpsc.collegediversity.Student
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
public class Student
extends java.lang.Object
implements sim.engine.Steppable

A college student currently enrolled at the University. Student objects are instantiated by the FreshmanFactory when they matriculate, and remain in existence until they graduate or dropout.

setRoom

public void setRoom(Room room)
Assign this student to a new dorm room. This method will inform the corresponding Room object that it has the new occupant, and if this student previously had a room, that Room object will be told that it no longer has the occupant.

step

public void step(sim.engine.SimState state)
Perform monthly activities for this student. In particular:
  • Assign all upperclassmen to dorms.
  • Increment the academic year.

Specified by:
step in interface sim.engine.Steppable

similarityTo

public double similarityTo(Student s)
Compute the perceived similarity (from this student's point of view) of this student to the student passed. This may differ from the other students' point of view because the two students may weigh race, grade-in-school, and/or GPA differently.
There are no guaranteed bounds on the return value from this method; higher values simply indicate greater similarity than lower values.

similarityTo

public double similarityTo(Group g)
Compute this student's perceived similarity to the students in the group that is passed.

joinGroup

public void joinGroup(Group g)
Add the group passed to this student's set of groups. This does not inform the Group object that it has a new member.

leaveGroup

public void leaveGroup(Group g)
Remove the group passed from this student's set of groups. This does not inform the Group object that it no longer has this member.
If the student is not a member of the group, this method does nothing.
